不行，你不能利用那一点 抢走帅哥跟最后一块蓝莓松饼

97
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,280
Did I use that already today? Sorry.
今天我已经用过那个借口了？对不起

98
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:41,160
"Ben, Carlos, David.."
班，卡洛斯，大卫…

99
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:44,830
Oh, I win. He's got Barney's on his speed dial.
我赢了，他在速拨键里记下了巴尼斯

100
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:47,500
You don't know it's Barney's the store.
你不知道他指的是不是巴尼斯服饰店

101
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,330
That could be his friend's house, a bar..
那可能是他朋友家或是酒吧的电话…

102
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:52,730
Who has Barney's the store on their speed dial?
谁会把巴尼斯服饰店的电话 记录成速拨键？

103
00:06:53,010 --> 00:06:55,070
His new girlfriend.
他的新女朋友

104
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,320
What is that?
那是什么声音？

105
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:13,350
I think it's the Dying Cat Parade.
我想是快死掉的猫在举行游行

106
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,190
Sounds like it's coming from across the street.
听起来是从对街传来的

107
00:07:18,670 --> 00:07:21,930
-Oh, my God. -What?
-我的天啊 -什么？

108
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:24,500
The thing that Ross was gonna do at our wedding?
还记得罗斯说他要在 婚礼上给我们惊喜吗？

109
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:28,440
He was hanging out with me and said,  "You're half Scottish, right?"
他跟我出去混时说： “你有苏格兰的血统吧？”

110
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:32,370
No. There is no way. It cannot be Ross.
不，不可能，不可能是罗斯

111
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:44,050
Unbelievable. Why is your family Scottish?
不可思议，为什么你有苏格兰血统？

112
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:48,190
Why is your family Ross?
为什么罗斯是你哥哥？

113
00:07:49,730 --> 00:07:52,360
He cannot play at our wedding.
他不能在婚礼上演奏 大家都会跑光的

114
00:07:53,070 --> 00:07:55,760
I mean, come on. That is just noise!
我是说那只是噪音！

115
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,900
It's not even a song.
那根本不算是歌

116
00:07:58,970 --> 00:08:01,500
Wait. If you listen very carefully...
等一下，如果你仔细听…

117
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:04,740
I think it's "Celebration" by Kool and the Gang.
我想它是库尔 与伙伴合唱团唱的《庆祝》

118
00:08:10,850 --> 00:08:13,840
You're right. They are writing me out of the show.
你说的对，他们要将我踢出这出戏

119
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:17,490
They don't know exactly when it's going to happen, but soon...
他们还没有决定 什么时候，但应该很快…

120
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:19,280
and then that's it.
就是这样了

121
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:22,550
If it was up to me,  you would never leave the show.
我真的很抱歉，如果我可以决定 你永远都不会离开这出戏

122
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,890
-Yeah, thanks. -I mean it.
-谢谢你 -我是认真的

123
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,400
I can't believe they'd do this to you. And to your fans.
我不敢相信他们会对你这么做 还有你的影迷

124
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:33,010
They're gonna be devastated. Heartbroken. They love you so much.
他们一定会崩溃伤心 他们是那么地爱你

125
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:35,510
Oh, you're right.
你说的对

126
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,410
Thank you.
谢谢

127
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:39,440
What's your name again?
你说你叫什么名字？

128
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:42,280
-Joey. -Thank you.
-乔伊 -谢谢你

129
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:44,710
That is so sweet.
那真的太贴心了

130
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,950
The only reason I came up to you before...
听着，之前我会来找你...

131
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:49,810
is because, well...
是因为…

132
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:53,120
I'm really nervous about being you.
因为要饰演你我真的很紧张

133
00:08:53,330 --> 00:08:57,390
If you could help me capture the essence of the character...
请你帮我抓住角色的精髓

134
00:08:57,630 --> 00:09:00,260
Help me keep Jessica alive. Please?
帮助我让洁西卡 继续活下去，可以吗？

135
00:09:02,740 --> 00:09:04,200
Joey, I will help you.
好吧，乔伊，我会帮你

136
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:07,910
Not because I owe it to this stupid show...
不是因为我对这出蠢戏有亏欠…

137
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:11,340
but because I owe it to Jessica.
而是因为我亏欠洁西卡

138
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,340
-Oh, thank you so much. -You're so welcome.
-那真的是太棒了，谢谢你 -别客气

139
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:17,240
I've been watching some tapes. How's this?
我一直在观摩录影带 你觉得这招如何？

140
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:21,640
Jessica Lockhart will never step foot in this place again!
洁西卡拉哈特 永远都不会再踏入这里！

141
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:23,080
Never!
永远都不会！

142
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,190
Jessica doesn't have an English accent.
但洁西卡没有英国腔

143
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,520
I can do an English accent?
我有英国腔？

144
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:36,330
That baby's going on my resume.
我要把这点写在我的履历表里

145
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:42,410
-Hi. How are you? -Good.
-嗨，你好吗？ -我很好

146
00:09:42,610 --> 00:09:45,080
Remember when we were in the coffeehouse...
还记得我们在咖啡厅时…

147
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:48,370
we decided I was gonna keep the cute guy's phone?
我们决定我可以 拿走那个帅哥的手机吗？

148
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:53,180
I was gonna keep it in my purse, so if it rang, I could just pick it up?
我要把它放在我的皮包里 如果它响了，我就能立刻接听？

149
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:58,620
Do you remember going into my purse and stealing the phone?
你还记得你从我的皮包 把手机偷走了吗？

150
00:10:00,090 --> 00:10:01,430
Ooh, now you lost me.
我听不懂你在说什么

151
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:04,020
-You stole the phone. -No, I didn't.
-你偷走了手机 -不，我没有

152
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:07,260
You're saying if I called it,  it wouldn't ring?
如果我拨号过去它不会响吗？

153
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:08,590
-No. -Okay.
-不会 -好吧

154
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:13,400
But while you dial, let me show you the features of my new ringing handbag.
既然你要拨号了，我要让你看看 我刚买的响铃皮包

155
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:17,130
Oh, it does work.
喔，它真的有用

156
00:10:18,580 --> 00:10:20,510
-Phoebe. -That is a different phone.
-菲比 -那是另一只手机

157
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:25,520
Oh, is it? Hello. Yes, hi. Is Rachel there?
是吗？喂，对，你好，瑞秋在吗？

158
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:29,120
Yes, she is. Just one moment, please. It's for me!
她在，请稍等，是找我的！

159
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,920
That is damning evidence.
那是铁证

160
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:38,020
Oh, my God. I bet that's him.
